{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784313994063,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_8ff72e6a74314648991d7030","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Deep Research Dashboard — glm-max lineage\n\n**Lineage:** glm-max (cli-opencode / GLM-5.2) | **Mode:** research, divergent Run 2 | **Stop policy:** max-iterations (5)\n**Session:** fanout-glm-max-1784313510669-wn3vsj | **Started:** 2026-07-17T18:41:00Z\n\n> Convergence is telemetry only under `stopPolicy: max-iterations`. The loop runs all 5 iterations.\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status | thread |\n|-----|-------|--------------|----------|--------|--------|\n| 1 | Layer-0↔Layer-1 coupling under null defaultMode | 0.85 | 4 | complete | 2 |\n\n## Question Status\n\n1/5 answered — **Q1 resolved.** Q2–Q5 open.\n\n**Resolved:** Q1 (no re-escalation to Layer-0; defer terminates at user; advisor already pre-resolves modes for system-deep-loop via bespoke layer).\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 0.85 → (ascending frontier)\n- Direction: opening iteration — high novelty expected; convergence is advisory only.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- \"null pushes cost to Layer-0\" (thread 2 framing) — ruled out: defer terminates at user, not advisor.\n\n## Blocked Stops\n\nNone (max-iterations policy).\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 2 → Q2 (thread 6): cross-hub generalization. Is detection-routed (sk-code) the universal archetype, making Run 1's proposed third archetype redundant? Test sk-design detection feasibility.\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled