{"type":"text","timestamp":1784314050480,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"id":"prt_f7167b7aa001iigc5Mw1vtlO7V","messageID":"msg_f7167977c0010sUrwjYheodrbN","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","type":"text","text":"**Iteration 2 → Q2 (thread 6): detection-routed as universal archetype.** Grounding reads on sk-code's surface detection and sk-design's registry.","time":{"start":1784314050474,"end":1784314050479}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314050483,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ce67fd4984714f469fbf46e3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: sk-code\n3: description: \"Unified two-axis code skill: routes to two WORKFLOW modes (quality, code-review) and bundles two read-only SURFACE evidence packets (code-webflow, code-opencode) — each surface carrying the implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine plus its stack knowledge — over shared surface-detection; holds no per-mode logic; dispatches by workflowMode through mode-registry.json.\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n5: version: 4.1.0.0\n6: metadata:\n7:   author: OpenCode\n8:   family: sk-code\n9: ---\n10: \n11: <!-- Keywords: sk-code, code, surface-aware, two-axis, webflow, opencode, animation, motion.dev, frontend, browser, typescript, python, shell, json, jsonc, code-quality, code-review, quality, review, verification, debug, implement, workflow-doctrine, mode-registry, workflowmode, packetkind, backendkind, surface-router, evidence-base, surface-packet -->\n12: \n13: # Code Family Hub (sk-code)\n14: \n15: One skill, two axes, one shared surface-detection router, and one advisor identity. The **workflow axis** is two code modes that act (quality, code-review); the **surface axis** is two read-only evidence packets the hub bundles alongside a workflow mode (code-webflow, code-opencode). Each surface carries the shared **implement → debug → verify** workflow doctrine (`shared/references/workflow_*.md`, symlinked in) plus its own stack knowledge; code-webflow also carries the folded-in Motion.dev animation overlay. This hub holds NO per-mode logic: it routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`, and each mode or surface keeps its own contract in its packet.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n20: \n21: Use this skill for code-family workflows. Invoke it as `sk-code` with an optional mode hint such as `quality: <request>`; the hub classifies the request, resolves a mode key, and loads the matching nested packet.\n22: \n23: **Workflow axis** (modes that act — one is chosen as primary):\n24: \n25: | Mode | Use it for | Packet |\n26: |------|------------|--------|\n27: | **quality** | Quality gate; P0/P1/P2 author checks; comment hygiene; surface checklists. | `sk-code/code-quality/` |\n28: | **code-review** | Findings-first review; security/correctness baseline; checklists; output contract; PR-state gates. | `sk-code/code-review/` |\n29: \n30: **Surface axis** (read-only evidence the hub bundles alongside the primary mode — never a primary, advisor-invisible):\n31: \n32: | Surface | Carries | Packet |\n33: |---------|---------|--------|\n34: | **code-webflow** | Frontend evidence: CSS/HTML/JS standards, implementation and performance patterns, CDN deployment, browser debug/verify — plus the Motion.dev animation overlay. Bundles the implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine (read-only evidence) for the Webflow surface; the acting agent applies it. | `sk-code/code-webflow/` |\n35: | **code-opencode** | System-code evidence: TypeScript/Python/shell/config standards, hooks, alignment verification, authoring checklists. Bundles the implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine (read-only evidence) for the OpenCode surface; the acting agent applies it. | `sk-code/code-opencode/` |\n36: \n37: The **implement → debug → verify** phases are not standalone modes. Their surface-agnostic doctrine lives once in `shared/references/workflow_implement.md`, `workflow_debug.md`, and `workflow_verify.md`, and is symlinked into each surface so the active surface carries the full workflow. A request to implement, debug, or verify code detects its surface and loads that surface's bundled doctrine; the acting agent applies it.\n38: \n39: ### When NOT to Use\n40: - Documentation-only changes with no code-work contract - use `sk-doc`.\n41: - Git workflow, branch, commit, PR, merge, or release work - use `sk-git`.\n42: - Pure browser inspection or external MCP transport work - use the relevant MCP skill.\n43: - Design judgment, visual direction, motion taste, or UI audit - use `sk-design` first.\n44: - Backend support primitives in `shared/` - they are consumed by the modes, not invoked as a user workflow.\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n49: \n50: Routing is **registry-driven**. `mode-registry.json` is the single source of truth; the hub reads it and does not re-derive the mapping. The advisor routes any code query to the single identity `sk-code`; the hub then picks the mode. This hub is a simple intent-to-packet router, not a root `references/<key>/` resource router: root `references/` and `assets/` directories are intentionally absent here, and resource slicing lives inside the nested packets plus `shared/references/smart_routing.md`.\n51: \n52: ### The discriminator\n53: - **`workflowMode`** - the public mode/packet key: `quality`, `code-review` (workflow) or `code-webflow`, `code-opencode` (surface).\n54: - **`packetKind`** - the axis: `workflow` (a mode that acts) or `surface` (read-only evidence bundled alongside a mode).\n55: - **`backendKind`** - which backend runs the packet: `surface-router` or `review-cache` for workflow modes, `evidence-base` for surface packets.\n56: \n57: Surface packets are advisor-invisible (`routingClass: metadata`, read-only `toolSurface`): the advisor still routes the single identity `sk-code`, and the hub bundles zero-or-more surfaces as evidence via `routerPolicy.outcomes.surfaceBundle` (workflow mode ordered first, surfaces after). \"review my webflow animation for jank\" → `[code-review, code-webflow]`.\n58: \n59: ### Routing rule\n60: ```python\n61: from pathlib import Path\n62: \n63: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n64: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n65:     \"Confirm whether this is quality, code-review, Webflow, or OpenCode work\",\n66:     \"Confirm the target files or runtime surface\",\n67:     \"Confirm the expected action: implement, debug, verify, quality gate, or review\",\n68:     \"Confirm the verification command set before completion\",\n69: ]\n70: \n71: def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n72:     resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n73:     resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n74:     if resolved.name != \"SKILL.md\" and resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n75:         raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown skill resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n76:     return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n77: \n78: def load_if_available(relative_path: str, loaded: list[str], seen: set[str]) -> None:\n79:     guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n80:     path = SKILL_ROOT / guarded\n81:     if path.exists() and guarded not in seen:\n82:         load(guarded)\n83:         loaded.append(guarded)\n84:         seen.add(guarded)\n85: \n86: def route(task):\n87:     loaded, seen = [], set()\n88:     registry = read_json(SKILL_ROOT / \"mode-registry.json\")\n89:     workflow_mode = explicit_mode_hint(task) or classify_workflow_mode(task)\n90: \n91:     if not workflow_mode:\n92:         load_if_available(\"shared/README.md\", loaded, seen)\n93:         return {\n94:             \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n95:             \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n96:             \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n97:             \"resources\": loaded,\n98:         }\n99: \n100:     entry = find_registry_entry(registry, workflowMode=workflow_mode)\n101:     if not entry:\n102:         load_if_available(\"shared/README.md\", loaded, seen)\n103:         return {\"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\", \"unknown_mode\": workflow_mode, \"resources\": loaded}\n104: \n105:     packet_skill = f\"{entry['packet']}/SKILL.md\"\n106:     load_if_available(packet_skill, loaded, seen)\n107: \n108:     for surface_mode in surface_bundle_from_hub_router(task):\n109:         surface_entry = find_registry_entry(registry, workflowMode=surface_mode)\n110:         if surface_entry:\n111:             load_if_available(f\"{surface_entry['packet']}/SKILL.md\", loaded, seen)\n112: \n113:     if not loaded:\n114:         load_if_available(\"shared/README.md\", loaded, seen)\n115:         return {\"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\", \"notice\": \"matched registry but no packet SKILL.md was available\", \"resources\": loaded}\n116: \n117:     return {\"workflowMode\": workflow_mode, \"backendKind\": entry[\"backendKind\"], \"resources\": loaded}\n118: ```\n119: \n120: When no workflow mode dominates (a bare implement/debug/verify request), the router defers to a pure surface bundle: it detects the surface, loads that surface's evidence and workflow doctrine, and the agent acts. `routerPolicy.defaultMode` is `null` — the hub does not force a stale default; an unclear code intent asks for disambiguation.\n121: \n122: Surface detection (`WEBFLOW`, `OPENCODE`, `MOTION_DEV`, with `OPENCODE` over `WEBFLOW` precedence) lives once in the hub's `shared/` layer and is consumed by every mode and surface. Modes own workflow contracts, not surface identity.\n123: \n124: Per-mode behavior is **not flattened**: each packet keeps its own code-work contract, standards, evidence rules, and tool-permission guards.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n129: \n130: ### Layout\n131: ```\n132: sk-code/\n133:   SKILL.md               # this routing hub (no per-mode code logic)\n134:   mode-registry.json     # the two-axis discriminator + advisorRouting (single source of truth)\n135:   hub-router.json        # lexical routing signals + surfaceBundle policy for hub-local choice\n136:   description.json       # hub advisor descriptor\n137:   graph-metadata.json    # the ONE advisor identity for the whole skill\n138:   code-quality/          # quality mode packet     (workflow)\n139:   code-review/           # review mode packet      (workflow)\n140:   code-webflow/          # webflow surface packet  (read-only evidence; carries the workflow doctrine + Motion.dev animation overlay)\n141:   code-opencode/         # opencode surface packet (read-only evidence; carries the workflow doctrine)\n142:   shared/                # shared surface-detection router, cross-mode helpers, and the implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine (references/workflow_*.md)\n143: ```\n144: \n145: Each mode or surface packet is self-contained and carries no per-packet `graph-metadata.json`; only this hub carries one, so the advisor discovers exactly one code skill identity. The implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine is a single shared source under `shared/references/`; each surface symlinks it in rather than duplicating it.\n146: \n147: ### Backend\n148: The `surface-router` backend is the shared surface-detection router under `shared/`. It centralizes WEBFLOW, OPENCODE, and MOTION_DEV detection and precedence, and it carries the shared implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine that each surface consumes. The `review-cache` backend supports the code-review mode's non-mutating review output cache. The `evidence-base` backend serves the surface packets: read-only domain evidence (`code-webflow/`, `code-opencode/`) the hub bundles alongside the primary mode — the packet mutates nothing and never carries process; the acting agent applies the doctrine it bundles. Shared backend material provides surface identity, the workflow doctrine, and cross-mode helpers; it must never gain per-mode workflow contracts.\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 4. RULES\n153: \n154: ### ✅ ALWAYS\n155: - **ALWAYS** resolve a mode through `mode-registry.json`; never hardcode a router mapping in the hub.\n156: - **ALWAYS** keep mode contracts in the mode packets; the hub stays routing-only.\n157: - **ALWAYS** keep exactly one `graph-metadata.json` (this hub's) so the advisor sees one skill identity.\n158: - **ALWAYS** give every mode an `advisorRouting` block with `routingClass: \"metadata\"` and the correct `packetSkillName`.\n159: - **ALWAYS** keep the implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine as one shared source under `shared/references/`, symlinked into each surface — never fork per-surface copies.\n160: \n161: ### ⛔ NEVER\n162: - **NEVER** add a `graph-metadata.json` inside a mode packet or `shared/`.\n163: - **NEVER** put per-mode quality, review, or surface workflow logic in the hub.\n164: - **NEVER** hardcode a router mapping outside `mode-registry.json`.\n165: - **NEVER** reintroduce implement, debug, or verify as standalone mode packets; they are surface-owned doctrine.\n166: \n167: ### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n168: - A new code mode is needed - extend `mode-registry.json` and open a packet; do not bolt logic onto the hub.\n169: - Surface identity and workflow ownership conflict in a way the shared router cannot classify.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## 5. REFERENCES\n174: \n175: - Workflow mode packets: `code-quality/SKILL.md`, `code-review/SKILL.md`.\n176: - Surface evidence packets: `code-webflow/SKILL.md`, `code-opencode/SKILL.md`.\n177: - Shared workflow doctrine: `shared/references/workflow_implement.md`, `shared/references/workflow_debug.md`, `shared/references/workflow_verify.md` (symlinked into each surface).\n178: - Registry: `mode-registry.json` (two-axis: `packetKind` discriminates workflow vs surface).\n179: - Hub router signals + surface bundling: `hub-router.json`.\n180: - Parent-skill pattern: `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/references/parent_skill/parent_skills_nested_packets.md`.\n181: - Sibling example: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/`.\n\n(End of file - total 181 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: sk-code\ndescription: \"Unified two-axis code skill: routes to two WORKFLOW modes (quality, code-review) and bundles two read-only SURFACE evidence packets (code-webflow, code-opencode) — each surface carrying the implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine plus its stack knowledge — over shared surface-detection; holds no per-mode logic; dispatches by workflowMode through mode-registry.json.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\nversion: 4.1.0.0\nmetadata:\n  author: OpenCode\n  family: sk-code\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: sk-code, code, surface-aware, two-axis, webflow, opencode, animation, motion.dev, frontend, browser, typescript, python, shell, json, jsonc, code-quality, code-review, quality, review, verification, debug, implement, workflow-doctrine, mode-registry, workflowmode, packetkind, backendkind, surface-router, evidence-base, surface-packet -->\n\n# Code Family Hub (sk-code)\n\nOne skill, two axes, one shared surface-detection router, and one advisor identity. The **workflow axis** is two code modes that act (quality, code-review); the **surface axis** is two read-only evidence packets the hub bundles alongside a workflow mode (code-webflow, code-opencode). Each surface carries the shared **implement → debug → verify** workflow doctrine (`shared/references/workflow_*.md`, symlinked in) plus its own stack knowledge; code-webflow also carries the folded-in Motion.dev animation overlay. This hub holds NO per-mode logic: it routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`, and each mode or surface keeps its own contract in its packet.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: sk-code\ndescription: \"Unified two-axis code skill: routes to two WORKFLOW modes (quality, code-review) and bundles two read-only SURFACE evidence packets (code-webflow, code-opencode) — each surface carrying the implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine plus its stack knowledge — over shared surface-detection; holds no per-mode logic; dispatches by workflowMode through mode-registry.json.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\nversion: 4.1.0.0\nmetadata:\n  author: OpenCode\n  family: sk-code\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: sk-code, code, surface-aware, two-axis, webflow, opencode, animation, motion.dev, frontend, browser, typescript, python, shell, json, jsonc, code-quality, code-review, quality, review, verification, debug, implement, workflow-doctrine, mode-registry, workflowmode, packetkind, backendkind, surface-router, evidence-base, surface-packet -->\n\n# Code Family Hub (sk-code)\n\nOne skill, two axes, one shared surface-detection router, and one advisor identity. The **workflow axis** is two code modes that act (quality, code-review); the **surface axis** is two read-only evidence packets the hub bundles alongside a workflow mode (code-webflow, code-opencode). Each surface carries the shared **implement → debug → verify** workflow doctrine (`shared/references/workflow_*.md`, symlinked in) plus its own stack knowledge; code-webflow also carries the folded-in Motion.dev animation overlay. This hub holds NO per-mode logic: it routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`, and each mode or surface keeps its own contract in its packet.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\nUse this skill for code-family workflows. Invoke it as `sk-code` with an optional mode hint such as `quality: <request>`; the hub classifies the request, resolves a mode key, and loads the matching nested packet.\n\n**Workflow axis** (modes that act — one is chosen as primary):\n\n| Mode | Use it for | Packet |\n|------|------------|--------|\n| **quality** | Quality gate; P0/P1/P2 author checks; comment hygiene; surface checklists. | `sk-code/code-quality/` |\n| **code-review** | Findings-first review; security/correctness baseline; checklists; output contract; PR-state gates. | `sk-code/code-review/` |\n\n**Surface axis** (read-only evidence the hub bundles alongside the primary mode — never a primary, advisor-invisible):\n\n| Surface | Carries | Packet |\n|---------|---------|--------|\n| **code-webflow** | Frontend evidence: CSS/HTML/JS standards, implementation and performance patterns, CDN deployment, browser debug/verify — plus the Motion.dev animation overlay. Bundles the implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine (read-only evidence) for the Webflow surface; the acting agent applies it. | `sk-code/code-webflow/` |\n| **code-opencode** | System-code evidence: TypeScript/Python/shell/config standards, hooks, alignment verification, authoring checklists. Bundles the implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine (read-only evidence) for the OpenCode surface; the acting agent applies it. | `sk-code/code-opencode/` |\n\nThe **implement → debug → verify** phases are not standalone modes. Their surface-agnostic doctrine lives once in `shared/references/workflow_implement.md`, `workflow_debug.md`, and `workflow_verify.md`, and is symlinked into each surface so the active surface carries the full workflow. A request to implement, debug, or verify code detects its surface and loads that surface's bundled doctrine; the acting agent applies it.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n- Documentation-only changes with no code-work contract - use `sk-doc`.\n- Git workflow, branch, commit, PR, merge, or release work - use `sk-git`.\n- Pure browser inspection or external MCP transport work - use the relevant MCP skill.\n- Design judgment, visual direction, motion taste, or UI audit - use `sk-design` first.\n- Backend support primitives in `shared/` - they are consumed by the modes, not invoked as a user workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\nRouting is **registry-driven**. `mode-registry.json` is the single source of truth; the hub reads it and does not re-derive the mapping. The advisor routes any code query to the single identity `sk-code`; the hub then picks the mode. This hub is a simple intent-to-packet router, not a root `references/<key>/` resource router: root `references/` and `assets/` directories are intentionally absent here, and resource slicing lives inside the nested packets plus `shared/references/smart_routing.md`.\n\n### The discriminator\n- **`workflowMode`** - the public mode/packet key: `quality`, `code-review` (workflow) or `code-webflow`, `code-opencode` (surface).\n- **`packetKind`** - the axis: `workflow` (a mode that acts) or `surface` (read-only evidence bundled alongside a mode).\n- **`backendKind`** - which backend runs the packet: `surface-router` or `review-cache` for workflow modes, `evidence-base` for surface packets.\n\nSurface packets are advisor-invisible (`routingClass: metadata`, read-only `toolSurface`): the advisor still routes the single identity `sk-code`, and the hub bundles zero-or-more surfaces as evidence via `routerPolicy.outcomes.surfaceBundle` (workflow mode ordered first, surfaces after). \"review my webflow animation for jank\" → `[code-review, code-webflow]`.\n\n### Routing rule\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm whether this is quality, code-review, Webflow, or OpenCode work\",\n    \"Confirm the target files or runtime surface\",\n    \"Confirm the expected action: implement, debug, verify, quality gate, or review\",\n    \"Confirm the verification command set before completion\",\n]\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.name != \"SKILL.md\" and resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown skill resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef load_if_available(relative_path: str, loaded: list[str], seen: set[str]) -> None:\n    guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n    path = SKILL_ROOT / guarded\n    if path.exists() and guarded not in seen:\n        load(guarded)\n        loaded.append(guarded)\n        seen.add(guarded)\n\ndef route(task):\n    loaded, seen = [], set()\n    registry = read_json(SKILL_ROOT / \"mode-registry.json\")\n    workflow_mode = explicit_mode_hint(task) or classify_workflow_mode(task)\n\n    if not workflow_mode:\n        load_if_available(\"shared/README.md\", loaded, seen)\n        return {\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    entry = find_registry_entry(registry, workflowMode=workflow_mode)\n    if not entry:\n        load_if_available(\"shared/README.md\", loaded, seen)\n        return {\"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\", \"unknown_mode\": workflow_mode, \"resources\": loaded}\n\n    packet_skill = f\"{entry['packet']}/SKILL.md\"\n    load_if_available(packet_skill, loaded, seen)\n\n    for surface_mode in surface_bundle_from_hub_router(task):\n        surface_entry = find_registry_entry(registry, workflowMode=surface_mode)\n        if surface_entry:\n            load_if_available(f\"{surface_entry['packet']}/SKILL.md\", loaded, seen)\n\n    if not loaded:\n        load_if_available(\"shared/README.md\", loaded, seen)\n        return {\"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\", \"notice\": \"matched registry but no packet SKILL.md was available\", \"resources\": loaded}\n\n    return {\"workflowMode\": workflow_mode, \"backendKind\": entry[\"backendKind\"], \"resources\": loaded}\n```\n\nWhen no workflow mode dominates (a bare implement/debug/verify request), the router defers to a pure surface bundle: it detects the surface, loads that surface's evidence and workflow doctrine, and the agent acts. `routerPolicy.defaultMode` is `null` — the hub does not force a stale default; an unclear code intent asks for disambiguation.\n\nSurface detection (`WEBFLOW`, `OPENCODE`, `MOTION_DEV`, with `OPENCODE` over `WEBFLOW` precedence) lives once in the hub's `shared/` layer and is consumed by every mode and surface. Modes own workflow contracts, not surface identity.\n\nPer-mode behavior is **not flattened**: each packet keeps its own code-work contract, standards, evidence rules, and tool-permission guards.\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Layout\n```\nsk-code/\n  SKILL.md               # this routing hub (no per-mode code logic)\n  mode-registry.json     # the two-axis discriminator + advisorRouting (single source of truth)\n  hub-router.json        # lexical routing signals + surfaceBundle policy for hub-local choice\n  description.json       # hub advisor descriptor\n  graph-metadata.json    # the ONE advisor identity for the whole skill\n  code-quality/          # quality mode packet     (workflow)\n  code-review/           # review mode packet      (workflow)\n  code-webflow/          # webflow surface packet  (read-only evidence; carries the workflow doctrine + Motion.dev animation overlay)\n  code-opencode/         # opencode surface packet (read-only evidence; carries the workflow doctrine)\n  shared/                # shared surface-detection router, cross-mode helpers, and the implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine (references/workflow_*.md)\n```\n\nEach mode or surface packet is self-contained and carries no per-packet `graph-metadata.json`; only this hub carries one, so the advisor discovers exactly one code skill identity. The implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine is a single shared source under `shared/references/`; each surface symlinks it in rather than duplicating it.\n\n### Backend\nThe `surface-router` backend is the shared surface-detection router under `shared/`. It centralizes WEBFLOW, OPENCODE, and MOTION_DEV detection and precedence, and it carries the shared implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine that each surface consumes. The `review-cache` backend supports the code-review mode's non-mutating review output cache. The `evidence-base` backend serves the surface packets: read-only domain evidence (`code-webflow/`, `code-opencode/`) the hub bundles alongside the primary mode — the packet mutates nothing and never carries process; the acting agent applies the doctrine it bundles. Shared backend material provides surface identity, the workflow doctrine, and cross-mode helpers; it must never gain per-mode workflow contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n- **ALWAYS** resolve a mode through `mode-registry.json`; never hardcode a router mapping in the hub.\n- **ALWAYS** keep mode contracts in the mode packets; the hub stays routing-only.\n- **ALWAYS** keep exactly one `graph-metadata.json` (this hub's) so the advisor sees one skill identity.\n- **ALWAYS** give every mode an `advisorRouting` block with `routingClass: \"metadata\"` and the correct `packetSkillName`.\n- **ALWAYS** keep the implement/debug/verify workflow doctrine as one shared source under `shared/references/`, symlinked into each surface — never fork per-surface copies.\n\n### ⛔ NEVER\n- **NEVER** add a `graph-metadata.json` inside a mode packet or `shared/`.\n- **NEVER** put per-mode quality, review, or surface workflow logic in the hub.\n- **NEVER** hardcode a router mapping outside `mode-registry.json`.\n- **NEVER** reintroduce implement, debug, or verify as standalone mode packets; they are surface-owned doctrine.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n- A new code mode is needed - extend `mode-registry.json` and open a packet; do not bolt logic onto the hub.\n- Surface identity and workflow ownership conflict in a way the shared router cannot classify.\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES\n\n- Workflow mode packets: `code-quality/SKILL.md`, `code-review/SKILL.md`.\n- Surface evidence packets: `code-webflow/SKILL.md`, `code-opencode/SKILL.md`.\n- Shared workflow doctrine: `shared/references/workflow_implement.md`, `shared/references/workflow_debug.md`, `shared/references/workflow_verify.md` (symlinked into each surface).\n- Registry: `mode-registry.json` (two-axis: `packetKind` discriminates workflow vs surface).\n- Hub router signals + surface bundling: `hub-router.json`.\n- Parent-skill pattern: `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/references/parent_skill/parent_skills_nested_packets.md`.\n- Sibling example: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":181,"totalLines":181,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1784314050478,"end":1784314050482}},"id":"prt_f7167b7ac001iRIazkqL5Y0KhW","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","messageID":"msg_f7167977c0010sUrwjYheodrbN"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784314050957,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"id":"prt_f7167b98b001xLB97ceLo57mhj","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"91e27bb55d6aa8a1b9dac8b49ec98a2ca3313442","messageID":"msg_f7167977c0010sUrwjYheodrbN","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":106929,"input":668,"output":85,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":106176}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784314060550,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"id":"prt_f7167df01001OBshEVwCtMZRxN","messageID":"msg_f7167bb14001TmaMJlsHg5ZzWr","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","snapshot":"58bb4d22bfaaebc7128300ec6030f69cce2c7abe","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1784314066695,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"id":"prt_f7167effe001bTbmuZCkRI4BxY","messageID":"msg_f7167bb14001TmaMJlsHg5ZzWr","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","type":"text","text":"sk-code nulls its defaultMode and works because the surface signal is **machine-detectable** (CWD/markers). The key Q2 test: does sk-design have a detectable signal, or only keyword intent? Reading sk-design's registry.","time":{"start":1784314064894,"end":1784314066694}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314066702,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_49797d589f774ec6ac88b7cc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"skill\": \"sk-design\",\n3:   \"version\": \"1.4.3.0\",\n4:   \"resourceContractVersion\": 1,\n5:   \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection for sk-design. The hub reads this file to resolve a mode; the advisor routes any design query to the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode. All six modes route by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n6:   \"discriminator\": {\n7:     \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n8:     \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for the five design-judgment modes (interface/foundations/motion/audit/md-generator) that act on a design axis; 'transport' for a packet that bridges to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface rather than performing design judgment itself.\",\n9:     \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/), playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline), or od-cli-transport (drives the external Open Design app's od CLI and stdio MCP server).\"\n10:   },\n11:   \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n12:     \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n13:     \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. For sk-design the packet folder IS its packetSkillName — the prefixed name (e.g. folder 'design-interface' == packetSkillName 'design-interface') — so no mode has a folder/name mismatch and grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false throughout.\",\n14:     \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true only when a packet folder differs from its packetSkillName (a preserved legacy mismatch). All six sk-design modes use folder == packetSkillName (the prefixed name), so none has a mismatch — grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false for all six.\",\n15:     \"command\": \"The bound slash command for the mode, recorded even on metadata-routed modes (same field sk-doc's mode-registry.json carries); null when the mode has no dedicated command today. The five design-judgment modes each have a dedicated /design:* command; the sixth mode, the design-mcp-open-design transport, carries command:null and is reached only by mandatory pairing with a design-judgment mode, never by its own command.\"\n16:   },\n17:   \"extensions\": {\n18:     \"transform-verbs\": {\n19:       \"description\": \"Declares the transform-verb routing extension: framing-split verb aliases (interface-frame 'make it' applies the move; audit-frame 'should it be' evaluates it), with excludedAliases and aliasOnly carve-outs. Activates the in-place top-level transformVerbRouting block without relocating it — the hub router vocabulary, command projection parity, and playbook scenarios all read it at that location.\",\n20:       \"declaredField\": \"transformVerbRouting\"\n21:     },\n22:     \"transport-axis\": {\n23:       \"description\": \"Declares the TRANSPORT axis. packetKind:'transport' entries bridge to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface (backendKind:'od-cli-transport', routingClass:'metadata', mutatesWorkspace:false since writes land in the external tool, not this repo). They never perform design judgment themselves — every entry on this axis has its own mandatory-pairing contract requiring sk-design's own workflow modes before any design-affecting operation.\",\n24:       \"transports\": [\"design-mcp-open-design\"]\n25:     }\n26:   },\n27:   \"transformVerbRouting\": {\n28:     \"note\": \"Transform verbs split by framing: audit asks whether the move should happen; interface applies the requested move. excludedAliases governs free-text transform-verb framing only (e.g. 'make it typeset'); command-metadata.json's taskProjections is a separate layer governing which mode owns the SAME verb under an explicit slash command (e.g. /design:foundations typeset). The two intentionally name the same verbs for different resolution paths -- this is not a collision.\",\n29:     \"interfaceFrame\": \"make it\",\n30:     \"auditFrame\": \"should it be\",\n31:     \"interfaceAliases\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n32:     \"aliasOnly\": [\"clarify\"],\n33:     \"commandProjectionParity\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"delight\"],\n34:     \"excludedAliases\": {\n35:       \"foundations\": [\"typeset\", \"colorize\"],\n36:       \"audit\": [\"harden\", \"polish\"]\n37:     }\n38:   },\n39:   \"modes\": [\n40:     {\n41:       \"workflowMode\": \"interface\",\n42:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n43:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n44:       \"toolSurface\": {\n45:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n46:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n47:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n48:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n49:       },\n50:       \"packet\": \"design-interface\",\n51:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-interface/procedures\",\n52:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\",\n53:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n54:       \"command\": \"/design:interface\",\n55:       \"aliases\": [\"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"visual identity\", \"make it look good\", \"looks templated\", \"redesign the ui\", \"hero section\", \"landing page direction\", \"hero redesign\", \"ui build\", \"design variations\", \"less generic\", \"custom not templated\", \"visual direction\", \"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n56:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n57:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n58:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\"\n59:       }\n60:     },\n61:     {\n62:       \"workflowMode\": \"foundations\",\n63:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n64:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n65:       \"toolSurface\": {\n66:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n67:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n68:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n69:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n70:       },\n71:       \"packet\": \"design-foundations\",\n72:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-foundations/procedures\",\n73:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\",\n74:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n75:       \"command\": \"/design:foundations\",\n76:       \"aliases\": [\"design foundations\", \"color system\", \"oklch palette\", \"color token system\", \"dark mode palette\", \"typography scale\", \"font pairing\", \"spacing system\", \"layout rhythm\", \"information hierarchy\", \"responsive layout\", \"design tokens\", \"theme tokens\", \"grid\", \"container queries\", \"context adaptation\", \"data visualization\", \"chart type\", \"data tables\", \"token starter\"],\n77:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n78:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n79:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\"\n80:       }\n81:     },\n82:     {\n83:       \"workflowMode\": \"motion\",\n84:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n85:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n86:       \"toolSurface\": {\n87:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n88:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n89:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n90:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n91:       },\n92:       \"packet\": \"design-motion\",\n93:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-motion/procedures\",\n94:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\",\n95:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n96:       \"command\": \"/design:motion\",\n97:       \"aliases\": [\"motion design\", \"animate this\", \"micro-interactions\", \"transitions\", \"interaction states\", \"hover state\", \"focus state\", \"loading state\", \"choreography\", \"motion budget\", \"animatepresence\", \"exit animation\", \"reduced motion\", \"morphing icons\", \"motion performance\"],\n98:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n99:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n100:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\"\n101:       }\n102:     },\n103:     {\n104:       \"workflowMode\": \"audit\",\n105:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n106:       \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n107:       \"toolSurface\": {\n108:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n109:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n110:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n111:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n112:       },\n113:       \"packet\": \"design-audit\",\n114:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-audit/procedures\",\n115:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\",\n116:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n117:       \"command\": \"/design:audit\",\n118:       \"aliases\": [\"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"design review\", \"review the ui\", \"audit the design\", \"accessibility audit\", \"wcag contrast\", \"performance audit\", \"anti-slop detection\", \"ai tell\", \"production hardening\", \"design quality score\", \"ui quality review\", \"p0 p1 design findings\"],\n119:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n120:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n121:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\"\n122:       }\n123:     },\n124:     {\n125:       \"workflowMode\": \"md-generator\",\n126:       \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n127:       \"backendKind\": \"playwright-extract\",\n128:       \"toolSurface\": {\n129:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n130:         \"forbidden\": [],\n131:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n132:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n133:       },\n134:       \"packet\": \"design-md-generator\",\n135:       \"proceduresPath\": \"design-md-generator/procedures\",\n136:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-md-generator\",\n137:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n138:       \"command\": \"/design:md-generator\",\n139:       \"aliases\": [\"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\", \"capture website css\", \"design tokens from url\", \"create design reference\", \"style reference\", \"tokens.json\", \"design-to-markdown\", \"extract design tokens\", \"validate design.md\", \"design.md validation\", \"design fidelity check\", \"design.md report\", \"render design preview\", \"source of truth\", \"study design.md format\"],\n140:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n141:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n142:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-md-generator\"\n143:       }\n144:     },\n145:     {\n146:       \"workflowMode\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n147:       \"packetKind\": \"transport\",\n148:       \"backendKind\": \"od-cli-transport\",\n149:       \"toolSurface\": {\n150:         \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Bash\"],\n151:         \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Task\"],\n152:         \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n153:         \"bashAllowlist\": []\n154:       },\n155:       \"packet\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n156:       \"packetSkillName\": \"design-mcp-open-design\",\n157:       \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n158:       \"command\": null,\n159:       \"aliases\": [\"open design\", \"open-design\", \"od mcp\", \"od cli\", \"wire open design\", \"connect open design\", \"drive open design from the terminal\", \"design system from open design\"],\n160:       \"advisorRouting\": {\n161:         \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n162:         \"packetSkillName\": \"design-mcp-open-design\"\n163:       }\n164:     }\n165:   ]\n166: }\n\n(End of file - total 166 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"skill\": \"sk-design\",\n  \"version\": \"1.4.3.0\",\n  \"resourceContractVersion\": 1,\n  \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection for sk-design. The hub reads this file to resolve a mode; the advisor routes any design query to the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode. All six modes route by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for the five design-judgment modes (interface/foundations/motion/audit/md-generator) that act on a design axis; 'transport' for a packet that bridges to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface rather than performing design judgment itself.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/), playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline), or od-cli-transport (drives the external Open Design app's od CLI and stdio MCP server).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. For sk-design the packet folder IS its packetSkillName — the prefixed name (e.g. folder 'design-interface' == packetSkillName 'design-interface') — so no mode has a folder/name mismatch and grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false throughout.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true only when a packet folder differs from its packetSkillName (a preserved legacy mismatch). All six sk-design modes use folder == packetSkillName (the prefixed name), so none has a mismatch — grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false for all six.\",\n    \"command\": \"The bound slash command for the mode, recorded even on metadata-routed modes (same field sk-doc's mode-registry.json carries); null when the mode has no dedicated command today. The five design-judgment modes each have a dedicated /design:* command; the sixth mode, the design-mcp-open-design transport, carries command:null and is reached only by mandatory pairing with a design-judgment mode, never by its own command.\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"transform-verbs\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the transform-verb routing extension: framing-split verb aliases (interface-frame 'make it' applies the move; audit-frame 'should it be' evaluates it), with excludedAliases and aliasOnly carve-outs. Activates the in-place top-level transformVerbRouting block without relocating it — the hub router vocabulary, command projection parity, and playbook scenarios all read it at that location.\",\n      \"declaredField\": \"transformVerbRouting\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"skill\": \"sk-design\",\n  \"version\": \"1.4.3.0\",\n  \"resourceContractVersion\": 1,\n  \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the discriminator (workflowMode/packetKind/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection for sk-design. The hub reads this file to resolve a mode; the advisor routes any design query to the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode. All six modes route by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"packetKind\": \"The axis discriminator: 'workflow' for the five design-judgment modes (interface/foundations/motion/audit/md-generator) that act on a design axis; 'transport' for a packet that bridges to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface rather than performing design judgment itself.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/), playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline), or od-cli-transport (drives the external Open Design app's od CLI and stdio MCP server).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. For sk-design the packet folder IS its packetSkillName — the prefixed name (e.g. folder 'design-interface' == packetSkillName 'design-interface') — so no mode has a folder/name mismatch and grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false throughout.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true only when a packet folder differs from its packetSkillName (a preserved legacy mismatch). All six sk-design modes use folder == packetSkillName (the prefixed name), so none has a mismatch — grandfatheredFolderMismatch is false for all six.\",\n    \"command\": \"The bound slash command for the mode, recorded even on metadata-routed modes (same field sk-doc's mode-registry.json carries); null when the mode has no dedicated command today. The five design-judgment modes each have a dedicated /design:* command; the sixth mode, the design-mcp-open-design transport, carries command:null and is reached only by mandatory pairing with a design-judgment mode, never by its own command.\"\n  },\n  \"extensions\": {\n    \"transform-verbs\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the transform-verb routing extension: framing-split verb aliases (interface-frame 'make it' applies the move; audit-frame 'should it be' evaluates it), with excludedAliases and aliasOnly carve-outs. Activates the in-place top-level transformVerbRouting block without relocating it — the hub router vocabulary, command projection parity, and playbook scenarios all read it at that location.\",\n      \"declaredField\": \"transformVerbRouting\"\n    },\n    \"transport-axis\": {\n      \"description\": \"Declares the TRANSPORT axis. packetKind:'transport' entries bridge to an external tool's CLI/MCP surface (backendKind:'od-cli-transport', routingClass:'metadata', mutatesWorkspace:false since writes land in the external tool, not this repo). They never perform design judgment themselves — every entry on this axis has its own mandatory-pairing contract requiring sk-design's own workflow modes before any design-affecting operation.\",\n      \"transports\": [\"design-mcp-open-design\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"transformVerbRouting\": {\n    \"note\": \"Transform verbs split by framing: audit asks whether the move should happen; interface applies the requested move. excludedAliases governs free-text transform-verb framing only (e.g. 'make it typeset'); command-metadata.json's taskProjections is a separate layer governing which mode owns the SAME verb under an explicit slash command (e.g. /design:foundations typeset). The two intentionally name the same verbs for different resolution paths -- this is not a collision.\",\n    \"interfaceFrame\": \"make it\",\n    \"auditFrame\": \"should it be\",\n    \"interfaceAliases\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n    \"aliasOnly\": [\"clarify\"],\n    \"commandProjectionParity\": [\"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"delight\"],\n    \"excludedAliases\": {\n      \"foundations\": [\"typeset\", \"colorize\"],\n      \"audit\": [\"harden\", \"polish\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"modes\": [\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"interface\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-interface/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:interface\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"visual identity\", \"make it look good\", \"looks templated\", \"redesign the ui\", \"hero section\", \"landing page direction\", \"hero redesign\", \"ui build\", \"design variations\", \"less generic\", \"custom not templated\", \"visual direction\", \"bolder\", \"quieter\", \"distill\", \"clarify\", \"delight\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"foundations\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-foundations\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-foundations/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:foundations\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"design foundations\", \"color system\", \"oklch palette\", \"color token system\", \"dark mode palette\", \"typography scale\", \"font pairing\", \"spacing system\", \"layout rhythm\", \"information hierarchy\", \"responsive layout\", \"design tokens\", \"theme tokens\", \"grid\", \"container queries\", \"context adaptation\", \"data visualization\", \"chart type\", \"data tables\", \"token starter\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-foundations\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"motion\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-motion\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-motion/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:motion\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"motion design\", \"animate this\", \"micro-interactions\", \"transitions\", \"interaction states\", \"hover state\", \"focus state\", \"loading state\", \"choreography\", \"motion budget\", \"animatepresence\", \"exit animation\", \"reduced motion\", \"morphing icons\", \"motion performance\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-motion\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"audit\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [\"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": false,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-audit\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-audit/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:audit\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"design review\", \"review the ui\", \"audit the design\", \"accessibility audit\", \"wcag contrast\", \"performance audit\", \"anti-slop detection\", \"ai tell\", \"production hardening\", \"design quality score\", \"ui quality review\", \"p0 p1 design findings\"],\n      \"advisorRouting\": {\n        \"routingClass\": \"metadata\",\n        \"packetSkillName\": \"design-audit\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"md-generator\",\n      \"packetKind\": \"workflow\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"playwright-extract\",\n      \"toolSurface\": {\n        \"allowed\": [\"Read\", \"Glob\", \"Grep\", \"Write\", \"Edit\", \"Bash\"],\n        \"forbidden\": [],\n        \"mutatesWorkspace\": true,\n        \"bashAllowlist\": []\n      },\n      \"packet\": \"design-md-generator\",\n      \"proceduresPath\": \"design-md-generator/procedures\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-md-generator\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"command\": \"/design:md-generator\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\", \"capture website css\", \"design tokens from url\", \"create design reference\", \"style reference\", \"tokens.json\", \"design-to-markdown\", \"extract design tokens\", \"validate design.md\", \"design.md validation\", \"desi