{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314282218,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_b1a9e21362654b4486505f8d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 3 → Q3 (thread 7):** Second-order anti-patterns of `null + mode-map`. Run 1 said null's fallback should load the routing helper (`smart_routing.md` + `mode-registry.json`). Invert it: what NEW failure modes does that introduce — mode-map bloat, stale registries, over-deferring friction, and critically **mode-map-as-new-catch-all-bias** (the over-emission disease Run 1 cured, re-introduced at the fallback layer)? Does loading the full mode-map recreate the catch-all-anchor problem that justified keeping sk-prompt's default?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->","oldString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 2 → Q2 (thread 6):** Cross-hub generalization. Run 1 proposed a *third* archetype (\"defer-routed keyword hub\"). Iter 1 found the advisor already collapses 5→1 with a mode-projection layer. Push: is **detection-routed** (sk-code's surface detection) actually the universal archetype the four flips should converge on — making the third archetype redundant? Test whether sk-design has a detectable signal (visual-system request → foundations; \"design an X\" → interface) and whether detection strictly dominates defer for multi-mode keyword hubs. Evidence targets: sk-code SKILL.md surface detection, sk-design mode-registry + INTENT_SIGNALS.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -111,9 +111,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 2 → Q2 (thread 6):** Cross-hub generalization. Run 1 proposed a *third* archetype (\"defer-routed keyword hub\"). Iter 1 found the advisor already collapses 5→1 with a mode-projection layer. Push: is **detection-routed** (sk-code's surface detection) actually the universal archetype the four flips should converge on — making the third archetype redundant? Test whether sk-design has a detectable signal (visual-system request → foundations; \"design an X\" → interface) and whether detection strictly dominates defer for multi-mode keyword hubs. Evidence targets: sk-code SKILL.md surface detection, sk-design mode-registry + INTENT_SIGNALS.\n+**Iteration 3 → Q3 (thread 7):** Second-order anti-patterns of `null + mode-map`. Run 1 said null's fallback should load the routing helper (`smart_routing.md` + `mode-registry.json`). Invert it: what NEW failure modes does that introduce — mode-map bloat, stale registries, over-deferring friction, and critically **mode-map-as-new-catch-all-bias** (the over-emission disease Run 1 cured, re-introduced at the fallback layer)? Does loading the full mode-map recreate the catch-all-anchor problem that justified keeping sk-prompt's default?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n ---\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -111,9 +111,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 2 → Q2 (thread 6):** Cross-hub generalization. Run 1 proposed a *third* archetype (\"defer-routed keyword hub\"). Iter 1 found the advisor already collapses 5→1 with a mode-projection layer. Push: is **detection-routed** (sk-code's surface detection) actually the universal archetype the four flips should converge on — making the third archetype redundant? Test whether sk-design has a detectable signal (visual-system request → foundations; \"design an X\" → interface) and whether detection strictly dominates defer for multi-mode keyword hubs. Evidence targets: sk-code SKILL.md surface detection, sk-design mode-registry + INTENT_SIGNALS.\n+**Iteration 3 → Q3 (thread 7):** Second-order anti-patterns of `null + mode-map`. Run 1 said null's fallback should load the routing helper (`smart_routing.md` + `mode-registry.json`). Invert it: what NEW failure modes does that introduce — mode-map bloat, stale registries, over-deferring friction, and critically **mode-map-as-new-catch-all-bias** (the over-emission disease Run 1 cured, re-introduced at the fallback layer)? Does loading the full mode-map recreate the catch-all-anchor problem that justified keeping sk-prompt's default?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n ---\n \n","additions":1,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784314282216,"end":1784314282217}},"id":"prt_f716b40e4001xpi67miuKcHMHS","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","messageID":"msg_f716b1a0b001jpSyEp3Pdypv06"}}
