{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314587159,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_c23980bc596c460ab95248fe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json","newString":"    {\"id\": \"f3-registry-drift-user-visible\", \"text\": \"null+mode-map elevates mode-registry.json from internal routing artifact to user-facing menu; drift becomes a user-visible lie — needs drift-validation or single-source derivation.\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.80},\n    {\"id\": \"f4-cli-detection-defaulted\", \"text\": \"cli is detection-defaulted (runtime env signal), NOT pure-defer — a distinct fourth shape. Splits Run 1's uniform flip-4 into 1+3: cli=detection-defaulted (flip null + runtime-detection block); deep-loop/mcp-tooling/sk-design=pure-defer.\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n    {\"id\": \"f4-detection-targets-default-axis\", \"text\": \"Detection can resolve the DEFAULT axis (not just surface bundling) when an env signal for the default exists. Canon detection is not surface-specific — it resolves any routing axis from environment.\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.80},\n    {\"id\": \"f4-single-mode-no-router\", \"text\": \"Single-mode entity is a standalone skill, not a hub; canon threshold for adopting routerPolicy should be >=2 modes (a one-mode 'hub' inherits the maintenance coupling for nothing).\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.75}\n  ],","oldString":"    {\"id\": \"f3-registry-drift-user-visible\", \"text\": \"null+mode-map elevates mode-registry.json from internal routing artifact to user-facing menu; drift becomes a user-visible lie — needs drift-validation or single-source derivation.\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.80}\n  ],"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n@@ -76,9 +76,12 @@\n   {\"id\": \"f2-archetype-is-per-axis\", \"text\": \"Archetype is PER-AXIS (environmental signal => detect+null; intentional signal => default-if-catch-all else defer), not per-hub. sk-code is already a hybrid: detect surface, null-default workflow. Run 1's 'third archetype' is mis-leveled hub-wise but correct in spirit.\", \"iteration\": 2, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n   {\"id\": \"f2-design-not-detectable\", \"text\": \"sk-design's 5 judgment modes have only lexical/intent discriminators (no environmental signal), so detection-routed does not apply; null+mode-map is the terminal correct state, not a waypoint to detection.\", \"iteration\": 2, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n   {\"id\": \"f3-hubidentity-on-default-is-canon\", \"text\": \"Canon explicitly names hub-identity-on-default-only as the over-emission mechanism (template _routingPrecisionNote + signal note). defaultMode is the ONLY legal home for hub-generic vocab — so flipping to null evicts that home (the point, and the seed of all second-order costs).\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.90},\n   {\"id\": \"f3-menu-vs-scorer-split\", \"text\": \"Run 1's 'load smart_routing.md + mode-registry.json' is correct ONLY with a semantics split: smart_routing.md is a safe scored resource (DEFAULT_RESOURCE=[]); mode-registry.json must be a PRESENTED disambiguation-card, never a scored resource (else hub-identity vocab recreates the bias).\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n-  {\"id\": \"f3-registry-drift-user-visible\", \"text\": \"null+mode-map elevates mode-registry.json from internal routing artifact to user-facing menu; drift becomes a user-visible lie — needs drift-validation or single-source derivation.\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.80}\n+  {\"id\": \"f3-registry-drift-user-visible\", \"text\": \"null+mode-map elevates mode-registry.json from internal routing artifact to user-facing menu; drift becomes a user-visible lie — needs drift-validation or single-source derivation.\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.80},\n+  {\"id\": \"f4-cli-detection-defaulted\", \"text\": \"cli is detection-defaulted (runtime env signal), NOT pure-defer — a distinct fourth shape. Splits Run 1's uniform flip-4 into 1+3: cli=detection-defaulted (flip null + runtime-detection block); deep-loop/mcp-tooling/sk-design=pure-defer.\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n+  {\"id\": \"f4-detection-targets-default-axis\", \"text\": \"Detection can resolve the DEFAULT axis (not just surface bundling) when an env signal for the default exists. Canon detection is not surface-specific — it resolves any routing axis from environment.\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.80},\n+  {\"id\": \"f4-single-mode-no-router\", \"text\": \"Single-mode entity is a standalone skill, not a hub; canon threshold for adopting routerPolicy should be >=2 modes (a one-mode 'hub' inherits the maintenance coupling for nothing).\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.75}\n ],\n \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n   {\"approach\": \"null defaultMode pushes disambiguation cost to Layer-0\", \"reason\": \"Hub defer terminates at the user via UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST, not the advisor; re-escalation only if a bespoke deep-routing layer is also built\", \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md\", \"iteration\": 1},\n   {\"approach\": \"all flipped hubs converge on detection-routed (sk-code pattern)\", \"reason\": \"Detection requires an environmental signal; cli/deep-loop/mcp/design have only intentional discriminators with no machine-detectable handle\", \"evidence\": \"iteration-002.md\", \"iteration\": 2},\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n@@ -76,9 +76,12 @@\n   {\"id\": \"f2-archetype-is-per-axis\", \"text\": \"Archetype is PER-AXIS (environmental signal => detect+null; intentional signal => default-if-catch-all else defer), not per-hub. sk-code is already a hybrid: detect surface, null-default workflow. Run 1's 'third archetype' is mis-leveled hub-wise but correct in spirit.\", \"iteration\": 2, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n   {\"id\": \"f2-design-not-detectable\", \"text\": \"sk-design's 5 judgment modes have only lexical/intent discriminators (no environmental signal), so detection-routed does not apply; null+mode-map is the terminal correct state, not a waypoint to detection.\", \"iteration\": 2, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n   {\"id\": \"f3-hubidentity-on-default-is-canon\", \"text\": \"Canon explicitly names hub-identity-on-default-only as the over-emission mechanism (template _routingPrecisionNote + signal note). defaultMode is the ONLY legal home for hub-generic vocab — so flipping to null evicts that home (the point, and the seed of all second-order costs).\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.90},\n   {\"id\": \"f3-menu-vs-scorer-split\", \"text\": \"Run 1's 'load smart_routing.md + mode-registry.json' is correct ONLY with a semantics split: smart_routing.md is a safe scored resource (DEFAULT_RESOURCE=[]); mode-registry.json must be a PRESENTED disambiguation-card, never a scored resource (else hub-identity vocab recreates the bias).\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n-  {\"id\": \"f3-registry-drift-user-visible\", \"text\": \"null+mode-map elevates mode-registry.json from internal routing artifact to user-facing menu; drift becomes a user-visible lie — needs drift-validation or single-source derivation.\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.80}\n+  {\"id\": \"f3-registry-drift-user-visible\", \"text\": \"null+mode-map elevates mode-registry.json from internal routing artifact to user-facing menu; drift becomes a user-visible lie — needs drift-validation or single-source derivation.\", \"iteration\": 3, \"confidence\": 0.80},\n+  {\"id\": \"f4-cli-detection-defaulted\", \"text\": \"cli is detection-defaulted (runtime env signal), NOT pure-defer — a distinct fourth shape. Splits Run 1's uniform flip-4 into 1+3: cli=detection-defaulted (flip null + runtime-detection block); deep-loop/mcp-tooling/sk-design=pure-defer.\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n+  {\"id\": \"f4-detection-targets-default-axis\", \"text\": \"Detection can resolve the DEFAULT axis (not just surface bundling) when an env signal for the default exists. Canon detection is not surface-specific — it resolves any routing axis from environment.\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.80},\n+  {\"id\": \"f4-single-mode-no-router\", \"text\": \"Single-mode entity is a standalone skill, not a hub; canon threshold for adopting routerPolicy should be >=2 modes (a one-mode 'hub' inherits the maintenance coupling for nothing).\", \"iteration\": 4, \"confidence\": 0.75}\n ],\n \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n   {\"approach\": \"null defaultMode pushes disambiguation cost to Layer-0\", \"reason\": \"Hub defer terminates at the user via UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST, not the advisor; re-escalation only if a bespoke deep-routing layer is also built\", \"evidence\": \"iteration-001.md\", \"iteration\": 1},\n   {\"approach\": \"all flipped hubs converge on detection-routed (sk-code pattern)\", \"reason\": \"Detection requires an environmental signal; cli/deep-loop/mcp/design have only intentional discriminators with no machine-detectable handle\", \"evidence\": \"iteration-002.md\", \"iteration\": 2},\n","additions":4,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784314587156,"end":1784314587158}},"id":"prt_f716fe8110014JFQVkn9ufTPYx","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","messageID":"msg_f716fb08d001Jj1qmI1slu7zdh"}}
