{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784314637733,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"id":"prt_f7170ada20012c5w7eqAfsnsnJ","messageID":"msg_f7170798f001ka9QD3SCZaerv6","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","snapshot":"7dbaeffc3f31922fdd6439ecf4b6f9b483398fdb","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314637735,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_a23dc632132c4e9c85b2352e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Deep Research Dashboard — glm-max lineage\n\n**Lineage:** glm-max (cli-opencode / GLM-5.2) | **Mode:** research, divergent Run 2 | **Stop policy:** max-iterations (5)\n**Session:** fanout-glm-max-1784313510669-wn3vsj | **Started:** 2026-07-17T18:41:00Z\n\n> Convergence is telemetry only under `stopPolicy: max-iterations`. The loop runs all 5 iterations.\n\n## Iteration Table\n\n| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings | status | thread |\n|-----|-------|--------------|----------|--------|--------|\n| 1 | Layer-0↔Layer-1 coupling under null defaultMode | 0.85 | 4 | complete | 2 |\n| 2 | detection-routed universal? sk-design feasibility | 0.80 | 4 | complete | 6 |\n| 3 | second-order anti-patterns of null+mode-map | 0.70 | 5 | complete | 7 |\n| 4 | edge cases breaking the archetype rule | 0.75 | 4 | complete | 9 |\n\n## Question Status\n\n4/5 answered — **Q1, Q2, Q3, Q4 resolved.** Q5 open (final iteration).\n\n- **Q1:** no re-escalation; defer terminates at user; advisor pre-resolves one hub only.\n- **Q2:** detection-routed NOT universal; archetype is per-axis; sk-code is hybrid.\n- **Q3:** 4 anti-patterns; canon names hub-identity-on-default; menu-vs-scorer split.\n- **Q4:** cli=detection-defaulted (distinct fourth shape); uniform flip-4 → 1+3 split; detection targets default axis; single-mode threshold.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n- Ratios: 0.85 → 0.80 → 0.70 → 0.75 (non-monotonic; divergent frontier, NOT a stop signal under max-iterations).\n- Direction: novelty stable; iter 4 recovered from iter 3's local low by splitting the flips. One thread remains (contrarian).\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- \"null pushes cost to Layer-0\" — ruled out (iter 1).\n- \"all hubs converge on detection-routed\" — ruled out (iter 2).\n- \"loading smart_routing.md recreates bias\" — ruled out (iter 3).\n- \"all four flips encode identically\" — ruled out (iter 4): cli is detection-defaulted.\n\n## Blocked Stops\n\nNone (max-iterations policy).\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 5 → Q5 (thread 12): contrarian steelman — strongest case that auto-default is fine. Refined by F4.1/F4.4: a default is fine WHEN environmentally determined and self-correcting (cli model). Where else might a named default be right? What falsifies the flips?\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-dashboard.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784314637732,"end":1784314637734}},"id":"prt_f7170ada3001hYBUovKNKu6wmF","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","messageID":"msg_f7170798f001ka9QD3SCZaerv6"}}
