wer\": \"Strongest falsifiable steelman: a default is justified when self-correcting (env-determined) OR genuinely catch-all. This OVERTURNS one flip — cli should be detection-defaulted, not null (its in-runtime default is env-determined and self-correcting). The three pure-defer nulls (deep-loop/mcp-tooling/sk-design) SURVIVE but are downgraded to directional-pending-measurement (Run 1's no-corpus method leaves them unfalsified in the over-deferring direction). Constructive output: a falsifiable four-shape decision rule replacing Run 1's uniform third archetype.\",\n+    \"evidence\": [\"iteration-001.md\", \"iteration-002.md\", \"iteration-003.md\", \"iteration-004.md\", \"file:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/run1-archive/research.md\"],\n+    \"iteration\": 5\n   }\n ],\n \"keyFindings\": [\n   {\"id\": \"f1-advisor-presolves-mode\", \"text\": \"Advisor already pre-resolves system-deep-loop mode (writes recommendation[mode]/[workflowMode]) via a bespoke, regex-gated layer — precedent exists but is not general.\", \"iteration\": 1, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json\n@@ -75,8 +75,17 @@\n     \"answered\": true,\n     \"answer\": \"cli is detection-defaulted (has runtime env signal) — a distinct fourth shape, splitting Run 1's uniform flip-4 into 1+3 distinct encodings. Detection can target the DEFAULT axis, not just surface. Single-mode entities are standalone skills (canon threshold for routerPolicy = >=2 modes). Registry drift becomes a gate not a lint under null+mode-map.\",\n     \"evidence\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/hub-router.json:4-14\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:87\", \"file:.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/parent_skill/parent_skill_hub_router_template.json:2\"],\n     \"iteration\": 4\n+  },\n+  {\n+    \"id\": \"q5-contrarian-steelman\",\n+    \"text\": \"Strongest case that auto-default is fine and Run 1's flip-4 is wrong. Where is a named default actually right?\",\n+    \"thread\": 12,\n+    \"answered\": true,\n+    \"answer\": \"Strongest falsifiable steelman: a default is justified when self-correcting (env-determined) OR genuinely catch-all. This OVERTURNS one flip — cli should be detection-defaulted, not null (its in-runtime default is env-determined and self-correcting). The three pure-defer nulls (deep-loop/mcp-tooling/sk-design) SURVIVE but are downgraded to directional-pending-measurement (Run 1's no-corpus method leaves them unfalsified in the over-deferring direction). Constructive output: a falsifiable four-shape decision rule replacing Run 1's uniform third archetype.\",\n+    \"evidence\": [\"iteration-001.md\", \"iteration-002.md\", \"iteration-003.md\", \"iteration-004.md\", \"file:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/run1-archive/research.md\"],\n+    \"iteration\": 5\n   }\n ],\n \"keyFindings\": [\n   {\"id\": \"f1-advisor-presolves-mode\", \"text\": \"Advisor already pre-resolves system-deep-loop mode (writes recommendation[mode]/[workflowMode]) via a bespoke, regex-gated layer — precedent exists but is not general.\", \"iteration\": 1, \"confidence\": 0.85},\n","additions":9,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1784314783432,"end":1784314783433}},"id":"prt_f7172e6c4001eChTQORCMqb7vC","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","messageID":"msg_f7172aff6001pRBOht7dRlgYlV"}}
