{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784314860911,"sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_d820dbc51a0f458aabcfeb13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Research Synthesis (glm-max lineage): defaultMode Divergent Run 2\"\ndescription: \"GLM-5.2 divergent lens (5 iterations, max-iterations stop) over the Divergent Exploration Agenda. Net delta vs Run 1: a falsifiable FOUR-shape decision rule (not Run 1's uniform third archetype); one real per-hub disagreement — cli recovered as detection-defaulted (NOT null); three nulls confirmed but epistemically downgraded to directional-pending-measurement. Plus a menu-vs-scorer fallback semantics split, drift-as-gate, and a single-mode canon threshold.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"defaultmode divergent glm-max synthesis\"\n  - \"four-shape defaultmode rule\"\n  - \"cli detection-defaulted\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"research\"\nlineage: \"glm-max\"\nrunType: \"divergent-run2\"\n---\n\n# Research Synthesis — glm-max lineage (defaultMode Run 2, divergent)\n\n**Executor:** cli-opencode / GLM-5.2 (`zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`). One of 4 parallel-detached fan-out lineages (sol-ultra, luna-max, glm-max, terra-max), each converging independently. This is the GLM-5.2 lens.\n**Method:** 5 iterations, `stopPolicy: max-iterations`, `convergenceThreshold: 0.05` (telemetry only — the loop ran all 5 by contract; convergence was deliberately not allowed to synthesize early). Each iteration opened a distinct thread from the spec's Divergent Exploration Agenda and was explicitly forbidden from re-deriving Run 1's verdict.\n**Baseline diverged FROM:** Run 1 (4 iterations, in `run1-archive/`) — keep sk-prompt; flip cli-external, system-deep-loop, mcp-tooling, sk-design to null; null's fallback loads the routing helper; add a \"defer-routed keyword hub\" third archetype.\n\n---\n\n## Bottom line\n\nRun 1's core verdict **survives** an adversarial GLM lens — but with one overturned flip, one epistemic downgrade, and a constructive replacement of its encoding.\n\n1. **One per-hub disagreement (the load-bearing delta):** `cli-external-orchestration` should be **detection-defaulted**, not pure-defer null. Its best default (\"the executor of the runtime you're inside\") is environmentally determined and self-correcting; nulling throws away cli's one genuine signal. Run 1 correctly killed the *static* bias but left cli's best behavior unencoded.\n2. **One epistemic downgrade:** the three pure-defer nulls (system-deep-loop, mcp-tooling, sk-design) stand as *directional-pending-measurement*, not *proven* — Run 1's deliberate no-corpus method leaves them unfalsifiable in the over-deferring direction. They are truth-reconciliation, not validated behavior improvement (the benchmark is blind to keep-vs-null, Run 1's own finding).\n3. **One constructive replacement of the encoding:** Run 1's uniform \"third archetype\" becomes a falsifiable **four-shape decision rule**, where each shape is nominated by a *testable condition* (is there an environmental signal for this axis?), not by imitation.\n\n---\n\n## Per-hub verdict table (Run 1 baseline → glm-max delta)\n\n| Hub | Run 1 verdict | glm-max delta | Confidence | The testable reason |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `sk-prompt` | KEEP | **agree** | 0.85 | Condition (b): genuine catch-all anchor with fresh route-gold receipts. |\n| `cli-external-orchestration` | FLIP → null | **DISAGREE → detection-defaulted** | 0.55 | Condition (a): in-runtime default is env-determined + self-correcting. Flip the *static* default, but encode a runtime-detection block, not null. |\n| `system-deep-loop` | FLIP → null | **agree (downgraded)** | 0.85 | No env signal, metadata already dead. *Directional-pending-measurement.* |\n| `mcp-tooling` | FLIP → null | **agree (downgraded)** | 0.85 | No env signal, already defer-with-suggestion. *Directional-pending-measurement.* |\n| `sk-design` | FLIP → null (+ move hub-identity) | **agree (downgraded)** | 0.85 | No env signal for 5 judgment modes; carries live over-emission bug. *Directional-pending-measurement.* Most likely hub to gain a detection signal later (URL → md-generator). |\n\n---\n\n## The constructive output: the four-shape decision rule\n\nThe encoding deliverable. Each shape is nominated by a **falsifiable condition**, replacing Run 1's single \"third archetype.\" The shapes are **per-axis** (a hub can be more than one — sk-code already is), not per-hub.\n\n| Shape | Default resolution | Falsifiable nomination condition | Example |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **keyword-with-default** | static named child (catch-all anchor) | one mode is the genuine dominant case AND serves as the legal home for hub-generic vocabulary (canon's hub-identity-on-default rule) | sk-prompt → prompt-improve |\n| **detection-defaulted** | `null` static + env-detected default | an environmental signal exists that resolves the *default* (not a specific mode) | cli-external-orchestration (runtime) |\n| **detection-routed (axis)** | `null` + env-detected mode | an environmental signal exists that resolves a specific mode/axis | sk-code surface axis (CWD/markers) |\n| **pure-defer** | `null` + disambiguation-card fallback | NO environmental signal AND no genuine catch-all | deep-loop, mcp-tooling, sk-design |\n\n**The discriminant that picks the shape:** *is the routing signal for this axis environmental (machine-detectable) or intentional (lexical)?* Environmental → detect (shapes 2/3). Intentional + one dominant → default (shape 1). Intentional + no dominant → defer (shape 4). This is testable per-axis, which is why the rule is falsifiable where Run 1's \"imitate the third archetype\" is not.\n\n---\n\n## Key findings (by thread)\n\n### Q1 — Layer-0 ↔ Layer-1 coupling (thread 2)\nFlipping to null moves **zero** disambiguation work to Layer-0. The hub's defer is a *terminal branch* at Layer-1: it asks the user via `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST`, never re-invokes the advisor (no infinite loop). The advisor already ships the same defer-with-clarification pattern Run 1 prescribed for hubs (`DEFAULT_RESOURCE_SEMANTICS = \"fallback-only\"`; `clarifying_question` on low deep-routing confidence), and already pre-resolves modes for **one** hub (system-deep-loop, via a bespoke regex-gated `_apply_deep_skill_routing_layer` that writes `recommendation[\"mode\"]`). That layer is hand-maintained and not generalizable without duplicating each hub's registry logic into the advisor. **[iter 1]**\n\n### Q2 — detection-routed universal? (thread 6)\nNo. Detection requires an *environmental* signal; sk-design's 5 judgment modes have only lexical/intent discriminators (color, motion, audit — all request vocabulary, nothing on disk). The archetype is **per-axis**, not per-hub: sk-code is already a hybrid (detects surface from CWD, null-defaults workflow). The four flips have no environmental signal, so null+mode-map is their *terminal* correct state, not a waypoint to detection. **[iter 2]**\n\n### Q3 — second-order anti-patterns of null+mode-map (thread 7)\nThe canon **already names the disease mechanism**: `hub-identity` vocabulary belongs on the default mode ONLY (template `_routingPrecisionNote`), because a shared class makes all modes co-fire on hub-generic words (the over-emission Run 1 cured). This makes flipping to null the eviction of hub-identity's only scoring home — the point, and the seed of four second-order costs:\n- **A1 — name becomes unrouteable:** the skill's own name (`design`, `prompt`) scores no mode → always defers. Bounded friction (one extra turn, a menu not a dead end), but the canon must name it as the *expected* cost so authors don't re-add a default to suppress it.\n- **A2 — menu-vs-scorer split (the central refinement):** Run 1's \"load `smart_routing.md` + `mode-registry.json`\" is correct ONLY with a semantics split. `smart_routing.md` is a safe *scored* resource (`DEFAULT_RESOURCE = []` — emits nothing on zero-signal). `mode-registry.json` must be a **PRESENTED disambiguation-card**, never a scored resource (loading it as a scorer with hub-identity vocab would recreate the bias). Introduce `defaultResourceSemantics: \"disambiguation-card\"` distinct from `\"fallback-only\"`.\n- **A3 — registry drift becomes user-visible:** under null+mode-map, `mode-registry.json` becomes the user-facing menu; drift is no longer internal. Needs the existing bidirectional-alignment checker run as a **gate**, not a lint.\n- **A4 — load a compressed card, not the raw registry:** one line per mode (purpose + 2-3 triggers), derived from the registry. Bounds token cost and removes the temptation to score the menu. **[iter 3]**\n\n### Q4 — edge cases (thread 9)\n- **cli is detection-defaulted** (the 1+3 split — see bottom line). Detection can target the *default axis*, not just surface bundling, when an env signal for the default exists.\n- **Single-mode threshold:** a one-mode entity is a standalone skill (system-skill-advisor has no `mode-registry.json`), not a hub. Canon threshold for adopting `routerPolicy` should be **≥2 modes** — a one-mode \"hub\" inherits the maintenance coupling (A3) for nothing.\n- **Empty/drifting map:** the disambiguation card must be **derived** from the registry (single source), and the alignment checker must gate. Empty-map = \"no modes configured; cannot route,\" not a silent empty menu. **[iter 4]**\n\n### Q5 — contrarian steelman (thread 12)\nThe strongest *falsifiable* steelman: a default is justified when self-correcting (env-determined) OR genuinely catch-all. This overturns the cli flip (→ detection-defaulted), concedes the three pure-defer nulls (they satisfy neither condition), and downgrades them to *directional-pending-measurement* because Run 1's no-corpus method leaves the over-deferring tradeoff unmeasured. A categorical \"keep all five\" steelman is unsupported. The constructive output is the four-shape rule above, each shape with a named falsifier. **[iter 5]**\n\n---\n\n## Eliminated Alternatives (primary research output — negative knowledge)\n\n| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Null pushes disambiguation cost to Layer-0 (thread 2 framing) | Hub defer terminates at the user via `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST`, not the advisor; re-escalation only if a bespoke deep-routing layer is also built (none exists for the four flips). | `skill_advisor.py:2810-2866`; `iteration-001.md` | 1 |\n| All hubs converge on detection-routed (sk-code pattern) | Detection requires an environmental signal; cli's is runtime-only, the other three flips have only intentional discriminators with no machine-detectable handle. | `sk-design/mode-registry.json:55-118`; `iteration-002.md` | 2 |\n| Loading `smart_routing.md` on null fallback recreates catch-all bias | Its `DEFAULT_RESOURCE = []`; it emits typed leaves only on a positive intent score and loads nothing on zero-signal. | `sk-design/shared/references/smart_routing.md:72-75`; `iteration-003.md` | 3 |\n| All four flips encode identically (Run 1's uniform treatment) | cli has an environmental signal (active runtime) the others lack; it is detection-defaulted, the other three are pure-defer — distinct encodings. | `cli-external-orchestration/hub-router.json:4-14`; `iteration-004.md` | 4 |\n| Categorical steelman: \"keep all five defaults\" | Three of five (deep-loop, mcp-tooling, sk-design) satisfy neither condition (no env signal AND not catch-all anchor); unsupported by evidence. | `iteration-005.md` | 5 |\n| \"The three flips are proven correct\" | Run 1's own no-corpus method makes them unfalsifiable in the over-deferring direction; the benchmark is blind to keep-vs-null. They are directional-pending-measurement, not validated. | Run 1 `research.md` (\"routes around needing a corpus\"); `iteration-005.md` | 5 |\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations (encoding deltas vs Run 1)\n\n### A. Per-hub router changes (the 1+3 split)\n1. **sk-prompt** — KEEP (agrees with Run 1).\n2. **cli-external-orchestration** — **DETECTION-DEFAULTED, not null.** Flip the *static* `defaultMode: null` AND add a runtime-detection block (`defaultResolution: \"runtime-detected\"`) that resolves the default from the active runtime. Neutralize the static `defaultResource: [\"cli-opencode/SKILL.md\"]` child-bias. This is the one real divergence from Run 1.\n3. **system-deep-loop, mcp-tooling, sk-design** — **FLIP to null + disambiguation-card fallback** (agrees with Run 1's flip, refines the fallback per B below). Treat as *directional-pending-measurement*: ship behind the route-gold gate, watch for over-deferring friction.\n\n### B. Fallback semantics (the menu-vs-scorer split — refines Run 1's \"load both\")\n- `defaultResource` for a pure-defer hub loads a **compressed disambiguation card** derived from `mode-registry.json` (one line/mode: purpose + 2-3 triggers), NOT the raw registry.\n- Introduce `defaultResourceSemantics: \"disambiguation-card\"` (presented to user, never scored) as distinct from `\"fallback-only\"` (a scored suggestion). Forbid `hub-identity` vocabulary in any resource loaded as a fallback scorer.\n- `smart_routing.md` remains a safe *scored* resource; the card is the *presentation* layer. Never conflate.\n\n### C. Canon encoding (four shapes, not three)\n- Replace Run 1's single \"defer-routed keyword hub\" archetype with the **four-shape decision rule** (keyword-with-default / detection-defaulted / detection-routed-axis / pure-defer), each nominated by the testable environmental-vs-intentional discriminant. Archetypes are **per-axis**: declare `routerPolicy` strategy per axis (workflow default vs surface), not one hub-level `defaultMode`.\n- Add `defaultResolution: \"static\" | \"runtime-detected\"` as a typed option distinct from `defaultMode`.\n- Set the canon threshold for adopting `routerPolicy` at **≥2 modes** (single-mode = standalone skill).\n- Promote the `hub-router.json ↔ mode-registry.json` bidirectional-alignment check from lint to **gate** (drift is now user-visible).\n- Keep Run 1's `defaultApplied → defaultConfigured` rename and the one-zero-signal-fixture-per-hub rule; add a fixture per shape (especially a detection-defaulted fixture for cli asserting the runtime-resolved default).\n\n---\n\n## Honest scope and confidence\n\n- **What's solid (0.80+):** the per-axis archetype reframe; the canon's hub-identity-on-default mechanism (line-cited); the menu-vs-scorer split; the single-mode threshold; the drift-as-gate upgrade; the epistemic downgrade of the three nulls (direct consequence of Run 1's no-corpus stance).\n- **The one contested claim (0.55):** cli = detection-defaulted rather than null. It depends on runtime-detection being robustly implementable across supported runtimes — plausible (the runtime is the process) but **not verified in this run**. Falsifier: if runtime detection is unreliable, cli falls back to pure-defer null and Run 1's original flip stands unchanged.\n- **What this run did NOT do:** no live-model routing experiment (thread 3 of the agenda — \"does a real model disambiguate cleanly or freeze?\"); no migration ordering analysis (thread 4); no full `defaultConfigured` rename ripple (thread 5); no multi-dominant/bundling deep-dive (thread 8). Those remain open for other lineages or a future run.\n- **Sibling lineages** (sol-ultra, luna-max, terra-max) converge independently; their findings are not read here. A cross-lineage merge (Run 2 synthesis) is the operator's next step, not this lineage's.\n- All router-change recommendations are **proposals** — changing a shipped `defaultMode`/detection block is a live-routing behavior change. Each ships behind the route-gold gate.\n\n---\n\n## Convergence report\n\n- **Stop reason:** `maxIterationsReached` (5/5; `stopPolicy: max-iterations`). Convergence was telemetry-only by contract; the loop was not permitted to synthesize early.\n- **Total iterations:** 5.\n- **Questions answered:** 5/5 (Q1–Q5 all resolved).\n- **newInfoRatio trend:** 0.85 → 0.80 → 0.70 → 0.75 → 0.65. Non-monotonic, descending modestly — consistent with a divergent frontier that broadened rather than converged. The final-iteration dip (0.65) is expected: the contrarian pass reassembles accumulated evidence rather than gathering net-new signal, and its load-bearing output is the *structure* (four-shape rule), not a new source.\n- **Average newInfoRatio:** 0.75. Under a `convergence` stopPolicy this would not have triggered STOP before iteration 5; under `max-iterations` it correctly did not.\n- **Composite stop score:** stayed at 0.0 by design (max-iterations suppresses novelty-driven STOP). `entropyCoverage` reached 1.0 (all 5 threads opened).\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md` — advisor routing model, fallback contract.\n- `file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2700-2867` — deep-routing layer, `clarifying_question`, mode projection.\n- `file:.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:50-122` — detection-routed archetype; `defaultMode: null` on workflow; surface detection.\n- `file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json:39-164` — six modes; lexical-only discriminators.\n- `file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/shared/references/smart_routing.md:72-75` — `DEFAULT_RESOURCE = []`.\n- `file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/hub-router.json` — `hub-identity` class on modes (live over-emission bug).\n- `file:.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/hub-router.json:4-14` — static default; no runtime field.\n- `file:.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/parent_skill/parent_skill_hub_router_template.json:2,5,37,60` — canon: bidirectional alignment, hub-identity-on-default-only.\n- `file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:87` — single-mode standalone skill precedent.\n- `file:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/run1-archive/research.md` — Run 1 baseline.\n- `file:.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/spec.md` — Divergent Exploration Agenda (§5).\n- Iteration evidence: `iterations/iteration-001.md` … `iteration-005.md` (this lineage).\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/research.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0063-skilled-router-collapse/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/research.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/021-default-mode-policy-research/research/lineages/glm-max/research.md","time":{"start":1784314860909,"end":1784314860910}},"id":"prt_f7174156c001RsH07Vtj6xvVEO","sessionID":"ses_08ea082cdffeOdjcwgjfes92M1","messageID":"msg_f7173306e001AjemRXPioxZDQb"}}
